gov.nasa.jpf.util

Class BitSet1024

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpf.util.BitSet1024
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FixedBitSet, Cloneable

    public class BitSet1024
extends Object
implements FixedBitSet, Cloneable
    a fixed size BitSet with 1024 bits. The main motivation for this class is to minimize memory size while maximizing performance and keeping a java.util.BitSet compatible interface. The only deviation from the standard BitSet is that we assume more cardinality() calls than set()/clear() calls, i.e. we want to cache this value Instances of this class do not allocate any additional memory, we keep all data in builtin type fields
